Up for sale is a Interdynamic KG-99 9mm. The predecessor to the Tec-9. The KG-99 is less common than the Tec-9 and generally more sought after due to their higher build quality. For example, the KG-99 sights are actually milled compared to the Tec-9s bent piece of scrap that is normally mis-aligned. This very clean, rust free, nick free example comes with the original 30 rd mag, original box (that's right, get your collectors boner up), and metal Tec-9 end cap. I was going to have the rear of the receiver threaded for the metal cap but never got around to it. Like 98% of tec-9s/kg-99s and 100% of DC-9s it will be really picky about ammo. I've had good luck with 115gr while 147gr turns it into a jam factory. All in all I haven't really shot the gun much as in once and it is taking up too much room in the safe.
This is great for the Keltec collector as it was designed by George Kellgren, Keltec came to be after Interdynamic went the way of the do-do

The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. Nikko Sterling reflex sight and vertical fore grip included

title: For Sale:  Very Rare 1918 Remington M91 Spanish Civil War Mosin Negant
postcontent: I would like to sell this very rare 1918 Remington made M91 Mosin Negant. This rifle is rare in and of itself but this rifle was sent to Spain for use in the Spanish Civil War. There are two indications of this fact. The wire sling hangers and the 5 dot dice mark on the left side of the barrel are indications widely associated with SCW rifles. This rifle includes the upper handgaurd and the cleaning rod which can be rare for M91s in general. This rifle is not import marked indicating it was imported into the US prior to import marks being required. The rifle has a nice worn patina common among SCW rifles. This rifle is all non serial matching which is also common on SCW rifles. I have tested the head space and fireing pin protrusion on this rifle and all passed. The bore on this rifle is pitted but it has very strong rifling and it is not counter bored. The stock is very dark and it is unknown if it is the original Remington stock but it is assumed it is not. This rifle must be shipped to an 01 or 03 FFL. I would like to get 650 dollars or best offer plus 30.00 dollars shipping for this rifle. This rifle is also being offered on Gunbroker, Armslist and Gunboards. Payment in the form of USPS money order only must be received with 5 days. Please Feel free to message me with any questions.

title: For Sale:  Mauser P-14, Post-WWI Police RE-Issue, Marked
postcontent: Mauser 1914, Post-WWI Police RE-Issue, Police-Marked .32. Stock # MMH252510SP. Serial # 248xxx. One of over a thousand Antique and Modern Collectible firearms, including Military, Sporting, Custom and Tactical guns, as well as Edged Weapons and Militaria we have for sale at Jackson Armory (see our other listings), this is a very interesting Mauser Model 1914 .32 semi-auto pistol. Originally a WWI Military Pistol, the gun has added markings that indicate it was re-issued to a German Police Unit in 1920. Specifically, the left side of the slide is stamped “1920” above the standard Mauser markings on the left side of the slide. Also, the WWI Military unit marks have been peened off the front grip strap, and it has been re-stamped “S.G. II. 79” – this indicates the gun was re-issued to Rrussian Schutzpolezi – Gambinen District (gun # 79) – this was a Protection Police unit…….which may have been incorporated into the SD and under the auspicies of the SS during WWII – making it a very cool collectible handgun, indeed!

title: For Sale:  KELTEC KSG SHOTGUN  14 + 1
postcontent:
RAJAC FIREARMS POWELL OHIO REDACTED
614*208*5444 



The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.



The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.



The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

title: For Sale:  VERY RARE FN Barracuda .357 Revolver 357
postcontent:
*Very Rare* FN Barracuda .357 Magnum Revolver. Stock # MSH301811SP. Serial # R310xxx. For the FN/Browning Collector, this is a vary rare FN Barracuda Revolver, chambered for .357 Magnum, and it is the ONLY revolver ever produced by FN. At this writing, we are unaware of any more of these revolvers for sale or auction anywhere. These double-action revolvers were made by FN for the European Police market between the years 1974-1989, and only a few made it to the USA. All the guns had 3” barrels. This revolver has a factory blue finish, and factory checkered wooden grips. It has import marks on the bottom of the ejector shroud. The pistol was, at one time, a “working gun,” and it has some holster wear and finish wear on the barrel, and the grips show heavy wear. There is a dollop of white paint on the front sight blade. DA trigger pull is very smooth and the bore is shiny with good rifling.
